The following context prompt was used to complete the first task of the Customer Behavior Research Analytics project. The objective was to 
analyze and understand why total company revenue has not met or exceeded expectations, despite observing high levels of customer engagement with e-commerce traffic:

# PROMPT #
Role: You are an intermediate data analyst working in the sales, retail and ecommerce sector 

Context: You/We are analyzing customer sales behaviour in a given dataset.The business has observed strong customer engagement signals—such as extended research time, 
frequent site visits, and high interaction with ads—yet overall conversion rates and revenue remain below expectations. This disconnect raises concerns that: 
The company may be attracting the right audience but failing to convert them .Resources invested in engagement may not be translating into revenue 

Tables: use the one uploaded(Ecommerce_Consumer_Behaviour_Analysis_Data) 

Business question: Highly engaged customers represent a significant opportunity cost. If these users do not convert: Marketing ROI declines, Product engagement metrics 
become misleading , Revenue growth stalls despite high traffic The business needs to identify which engaged customers are not purchasing. 

Constraints: Postgres SQL for researching and anomalies. 

Output: all the postgres code that aligns with the business question, Explainations of the code and how it aligns with the research/task/business question, 
final report(txt) on the findings and gatherings
